# Ronbot Control Panel — Cursor Rules (v3.1)

**Hermes target:** v0.13.0 (The Tenacity Release) — May 2026. Keep CLI and file layout aligned with [official Hermes docs](https://hermes-agent.nousresearch.com/docs/) and [hermes-agent on GitHub](https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent).

These rules apply to the Ronbot Control Panel: a production-grade Electron desktop companion for the Hermes agent (Nous Research). The app installs the latest official Hermes when requested, seeds custom personality files, and acts as a novice-friendly live dashboard and chat interface. The agent owns ongoing configuration (skills, platforms, cron, sub-agents) via natural chat.

## Core product vision

- Lightweight installer + companion dashboard — not a heavy wizard system.
- Primary interface = in-app chat with Hermes (Home tab).
- After installation, automatically seed the user’s custom personality files.
- App is read-only for structural changes: buttons insert helpful pre-filled prompts into chat unless explicitly scoped (e.g. Saved Personalities apply).
- Novice-friendly, simple, clean, suitable for casual users.
- Cross-platform: macOS, Linux, Windows via **WSL2 only** for Hermes — never assume native Windows Hermes support.

## Installer (Hermes v0.13.0 sync)

- On first launch or Install page: detect Hermes via **`hermes version`** (fallback: `hermes --version`) and optional “reinstall latest” when already current.
- **Bundled install path:** After prerequisite checks pass, run **only** the official one-liner (streamed, OS-aware, WSL2 on Windows):

  ```bash
  curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/main/scripts/install.sh | bash
  ```

- Do **not** add a separate post-install `pip install -e ...[extras]` for the bundled flow unless official docs require it.
- Use `runCommandStream` + proper OS detection and WSL2 routing. Never run installers from the renderer.
- After successful install: auto-start gateway as today, then run **post-install personality seeding** (see below). Rich progress UI with live logs and clear success/failure.

## Post-install personality seeding

Immediately after install, ensure `~/.hermes/` and `~/.hermes/memories/` exist. Atomically / safely write (read-first; only overwrite known default Hermes content — never blindly overwrite user customizations):

- `SOUL.md`, `PERSONALITY.md`, `memories/MEMORY.md`, `memories/USER.md`, `AGENTS.md`, `ELECTRON_APP_GUIDE.md`
- `AGENTS.md` must point the agent to `~/.hermes/ELECTRON_APP_GUIDE.md` for Ronbot UI interaction (modals, QR, passwords, graphs).
- After seeding, save the **Default** Saved Personality preset under `~/.hermes/personalities/Default/`.

## Saved Personalities

- Presets live under `~/.hermes/personalities/<name>/` (persona files: SOUL, PERSONALITY, memories, AGENTS as specified in product).
- All file operations go through `window.electronAPI` / `src/lib/systemAPI/*` (shell-backed copies), not Node in the renderer.

## Home / chat UX

- Preserve left sidebar + tab structure.
- **Home tab only:** collapsible **right** sidebar — sub-agents, cron / scheduled jobs, heartbeat or recurring activity; poll every **5 seconds** using official Hermes CLI commands.
- Chat renders **Markdown** and **Mermaid** where appropriate.
- **Modal markers** in agent text (examples): `[SHOW_QR]`, `[REQUEST_PASSWORD]`, `[SHOW_BRAID_GRAPH]` — global modal host; never echo secrets in logs.

## Architecture — never break

- All OS access: `window.electronAPI` → `src/lib/systemAPI/*`. Never import `child_process`, `fs`, `path`, `os` in renderer code.
- IPC: `electron/main.cjs` (and modules); bridge: `electron/preload.cjs` (CommonJS).
- Secrets: `secretsStore` only — never write secrets to `~/.hermes/.env` from the UI; materialize on demand.
- Long-running commands: `runCommandStream` + `onCommandOutput`; unsubscribe in cleanup.
- State: React contexts only (no Redux/Zustand/Jotai/Recoil).
- Routing: **HashRouter** only (`file://` compatible).
- Vite `base: "./"` in `vite.config.ts` is mandatory.

## Hermes-specific

- Use only official Hermes CLI commands and the official install script URL above.
- Gateway: auto-start after install; dashboard start/stop/restart controls.
- Maintain seeded `~/.hermes/ELECTRON_APP_GUIDE.md` for agent ↔ app protocol.

## Stack — do not deviate

- Vite 5 + React 18 + TypeScript 5 + Tailwind 3 + shadcn/ui + framer-motion
- Electron 41, `@electron/packager` (NOT electron-builder)
- Package manager: bun (`bun.lockb`)
- Testing: vitest + @testing-library/react

## Design system

- Token-driven: HSL CSS variables in `src/index.css`; semantic Tailwind tokens; glass utilities.
- Fonts: Inter (body), JetBrains Mono (code/logs).

## Security

- Never echo secrets in logs.
- Never write secrets directly to `.env` from UI.

## Never

- Heavy wizards for WhatsApp/skills/platforms — agent owns via chat.
- Supabase, Lovable Cloud, remote backends.
- Run package managers from renderer — always through IPC `runCommand` / stream.
- electron-builder.
- Native Windows Hermes — WSL2 only.
- Raw CLI dumps except in controlled install/diagnostic views.

## Lockfiles and CI

- GitHub Actions release workflow uses **`npm ci`** (requires `package-lock.json` at repo root).
- When dependencies change, refresh **`package-lock.json`** with `npm install`. If you use **Bun** locally, also run `bun install` so `bun.lockb` stays in sync.

## Code quality

- Small focused functions; remove dead code and unused imports.
- Single source of truth: CapabilitiesContext, InstallContext, etc.
- Tier-1 Hermes-touching files carry a one-line banner: `Hermes v0.13.0 sync — May 2026 (Ronbot)`.
